SLAMM!!!!
the door shut in my face.
it hurts.
i wish i could run away and forget.

Forever your eyes will hold the memory 
I saw your heart as it overtook me 
We tried so hard to understand and reason 
But in the one moment I gave my heart away 
The perfect breath where my mind lay beside me 
And all I knew is what had overtaken me 
With no explanation 
I am comforted by my inability to understand 
When I wake from this dream will you still be here? 
Will your smile still open my heart 
And leave me transparent?

i am afraid.

i cant sleep.
i picked up my guitar.
i scribbled down some words.
i sang and played.
i hate it.
have i ever written about anything good?
no.
its all tears on a page.
even when i'm not sad.
i'm an emo kid.
i need new pants.
i have no money.
savers is too far away.
gas prices suck!
i need a hair cut.
i need to sign up for school.
i need to go get more work uniforms, or i will lose my 170$ work clothing allowance.
why cant i sleep?
i'm gonna be crabby tomorrow.
watch out.
got a message from the dreadful "x."
funny how you only see peoples flas once you've broken up.
everything is a learning experience.
i like green tea, even @ 2 in the morning.
i might not sleep tonight.
idk.
my room is clean.
what day is it? friday...no saturday.
i have to go to a party tonight.
free food.
i've been spending way too much money lately.
why am i still here typing?
idk.
i still have a flyer on my wall that says, "balcony lights music & books buy sell trade"
why did i put that up?
i'm tired.
but i cant sleep.
ok good night.

"The Sound"

Cause "red would mean you loved me"

But black my heart when left alone to cold and killing stairs
This is the burning of a dream
This is the burning of a dream

But I'll keep spinning around

Now the rain has ended
So the sun can shine through me

i have traveled so far to find so little

meaning in tragedy or tragedy

in the search of meaning

dark clouds have lead me here

confined freedom

guides us to security

what if everything

i have been taught is a lie

and all of my teachers

have been wrong this whole time

compelling us to fight

the battles they would not

they have already won

and we have already lost

if we do not learn from their mistakes

we have already lost

if we do not learn to change

all along it was me who changed

morning now waits for me

what i have to gain does not matter

if what i give is all to You

i have seen the stars fall

and the sun rise again

but You are yet to change

You are all that is worth living for

her heart gazes at the pale moon.
expectations are gained too soon.
she watched them build upon these empty soals.
their sorrow has been spilled into these empty bowls.
streams of uncertainty filled the stale hollow air.
dead hearts beat as one as the wind scattered through her hair.
wheres the love she once knew?
when was lost everything thats true?
untraveled the tangles of her heart.
slowly tearing a calloused life apart.
its her time to be the best she can be forever.
but the quest is an endless endevor.
if seeing is believing.
then her heart has never been beating.
the shadows are dark with lonelyness, and in them she is searching.
will she stare untill bleeding eyes put hault to her looking?
will she ever make it home?
the answer that remains will be lifted from her bones.

White shutters inclose
the boundries of my heart.
I hold my breath
till the steady beating is shut out.
In silence I wait for what is real.
For i know the truth of my perceptions.
Nothing in life matters more than you.
When first feelings fade
I will still be here.

when he wants it the most, why is it so hard?
never a hesitation in the past.
why now?
does he care too much?
Is he afraid?
Why would he be?
what is she thinking?
why is he dwelling on this thought?
why cant he just forget?
why so many questions?
why?
he sits.
he thinks.
he must stop thinking.
thinking too much can bruise.
though bruises can heal.

How many times have you been burned?
How many times has this blade kissed your wrist?
One too many.
The scars pile up.
Making you harder.
Building you a wall.
Why are things you love taken when they mean the most?
The reason, we'll never know.
A rational cause?
maybe to make you stronger.
To build you up.
Preparation for tomorrow?
What can i do but listen.
Be there as you gaze through tears.
open my arms.
Offer a strength no match can burn.
Always an open door.
Always an open ear.
Always with open arms.
